    "body": "closes #179, closes #102  - With this commit, the field `interpolant` is removed from `OutputVar`. This was done to prevent the largely unnecessary construction of an interpolant every time a `OutputVar` is constructed. With this change, a `OutputVar` should take up about 50% less memory.\r\n\r\nWith this change, there is a lot of room for preventing unnecessary allocations. This is because making an interpolant means any function that modify the elements of `dims` or `data` must always create a new `OutputVar`. Instead, the `OutputVar` can be mutated instead and no new `OutputVar` need to be made.",
